The paper discusses the selection of the most appropriate fuzzy quantification model for practical applications, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also compares different models based on their adequacy properties, which is a common approach in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the complexity of model definitions, which is a topic in computer science theory and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the practical applications of fuzzy quantification models, which can be related to social impact and decision-making (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of different models, which is a topic in control theory and fuzzy logic (cs.FL).
